-- Duvernay Shale Gas Land Sale Sets Alberta Auction Record, Globe Reports
-- Sean B. Pasternak
-- 2010-07-09T11:21:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/duvernay-shale-gas-land-sale-sets-alberta-auction-record-globe-reports.html

          
          
             A C$451 million ($436 million)
purchase for oil and gas rights on prospective land at Alberta’s
Duvernay shale set a provincial land sale record for the average
amount paid per hectare, the Globe and Mail reported.  
 One or more companies, whose names haven’t been identified,
made the purchase, the newspaper said.  
 The land’s primary commodity is natural gas, the Globe
reported.  
